Oona makes her first night-time trip to the sea - all on her own!
Oona tries to keep Baba clean on a muddy Spring day.
Happy is really excited to win the Best Tomatoes Ever prize.
Hairdressers: During a game of hairdressers, Bluey discovers that big-headed customer Dad has nits! To help treat them Bingo has to find her voice, while Bluey has to find her ears.
Bicycle Diaries: In frustration having lost a game, Oswaldo takes off on his own mini bicycle adventure.
Brunch Club: Left in a classroom, the kids think they are being punished and reveal their 'crimes'.
Daniel is playing astronauts with Miss Elaina, but his tummy starts to hurt. He learns that sometimes when your tummy hurts, it could mean that you have to go potty.
You Feelin' What I'm Feelin': Huey and Kenny decide to build a base, starting by stacking stones to create walls.
Dee encourages a friend to say 'p', and we go on an adventure around the sound. We eat some popcorn and pizza, and even have a pyjama party!
Glitch makes a sand castle around an oasis in the Sahara. Can the Go Jetters save the day?
When a lost bird takes a liking to Bo, it'll be up to Mojo to fly it to its home. But it's a stormy trip, and Bo will need to do some flying of his own!
Bella School Teacher: Oli is tired of her sister Bella taking up all the space in their house and preventing her from having fun in her own way.
The Thingy: Titus finds a strange object that he doesn't quite know how to use. But Cochonchon, Fifi and Virgilier, in turn, have a great idea for using it and want to claim it for themselves.

programmes.show_name: Lex and Plu Space Taxi Drivers
programmes.show_description: The School of Cool: Lex and Plu need to take a passenger to a food festival. Lex always prefers to ignore rules of any kind and joyride. And today's no different.
Stargazing: Inspector Feathers takes the campers out stargazing, but accidentally breaks her compass. Odo uses the stars and constellations to lead them back to camp.
The Bug Hotel: Odo and Doodle build a bug hotel for a bunch of homeless beetles, but Louie and Bud don't like the 'creepy crawlies' at all.
When Hugo can't find his favourite Sunday Socks, he learns that his socks aren't what make Sunday's fun in the first place. (SL)
After Sonia's origami sheep has to be unfolded, she realises that some things can be re-made. (SL)
Strong Bottle Note: At the beach, Fuzzy Yellow finds a bottle with an unreadable note inside. Patoto gives Fuzzy Yellow an important hint about deciphering it. (SL)
